  "content": "\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://chaos.social/@ryan_harg\" class=\"u-url mention\"\u003e@\u003cspan\u003eryan_harg\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e Why do you need the for loop and sleep?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eYou could just do:\u003cbr /\u003esigc := make(chan os.Signal)\u003cbr /\u003esignal.Notify(sigc, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\u003cbr /\u003e\u0026lt;-sigc\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAlso, this might be better if you want a context:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003ectx, stop := signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(), syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\u003cbr /\u003edefer stop()\u003cbr /\u003e// do stuff\u003cbr /\u003e\u0026lt;-ctx.Done()\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://pkg.go.dev/os/signal#example-NotifyContext\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"ellipsis\"\u003epkg.go.dev/os/signal#example-N\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003eotifyContext\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
